tagDescription: First World War - "Some Historical Reflections relating to the War", an address delivered by Sifton to the Women's Canadian Historical Society of Ottawa, 1915; memorial of the 27th Battery, Canadian Field Artillery, 1919.
Imperial Conference of 1923 - summary of proceedings and a diary kept by Clifford Sifton.
Halibut Fisheries Treaty - Sessinal Papers III, containing Copies of correspondence between Canada and Great Britain .
Canadian Patriotic Fund - bulletins, Nov. 1917, March - May 1918, Feb, April - May 1919.
Whalen Pulp and Paper Mills - bond issue.
British Commonwealth - " The British Commonwealth of Nations. Features of External Relations", an address delivered by Robert Sir Borden before the American Historical Association.
War bonds and taxes - prospectus.
British Empire Association - prospectus Concerning the Association's objectives of land settlement and emigration within the Empire. See also: Immigration and Imperial Colonization Corporation.
William Davies Company Incorporated - prospectus of stock issue and Annual report.
Imperial Conference of 1926 - memorandum submitted on behalf of the Department of Marine and Fisheries.
American Investment in Canada - memorandum.
Trenton Chemical Company - statement.
Wood, Gundy and Company - List of federal, provincial and municipal bound offerings.
Klondyke Government Concession Limited - legal brief.
National Transcontinental Railway - memorandum.
Election of 1925 - speeches of prominent Conservatives, including Arthur Meighen, C. C. Ballantyne, Henry Drayton, Robert Rogers, H. H. Stevens and Gideon Robertson.

Constitution - memoranda, speeches, Sifton's article " Some Canadian Constitutional Problems" , in Canadian Historical Review, vol.3 no.1, 1922, page 3 - 23, and Sifton's addresses " Constitutional Relations of Canada", delivered to the Canada First League, 9 Jan.1923, and " The Political Status of Canada" delivered to the Canadian Club of Ottawa, 8 April 1922.
Peace River Oil Exchange Limited - prospectus and clippings.

Immigration - advertising " Why go to Canada?", n. d., and Siftons's address " The Immigrants Canada wants", delivered before the Toronto Board of Trade, 1922. See also British Empire Association and Imperial Colonization Corporation.
Imperial Colonization Corporation of Canada Limited - prospectus. See also Immigration and British Empire Association.
Northwestern Utilities Limited - statement.
Northern Crown Bank - Annual reports.
North Atlantic Steamship Combine - report by W. T. R. Preston.
Indian Mines Limited - Annual reports.
Canadian - American relations - clipping of an address by Robert Sir Falconer.
Western Union Telegraph Company - Annual report.
New Dominion Syndicate Limited - contract granting Sifton the power of attorney, list of shareholders and contractual agreements.
Peat Fuels Limited - promotional literature.
Imperial Conference of 1921 - summary of proceedings.
Election of 1926 - speeches Concerning Meighen's policies.
"Water Power in Canada" - memorandum.
Northern Commercial Telegraph Company Limited - prospectus.
